1.Text: Eta, pass me that orange.
...No, I don't wanna move.
Don't say that. You're the closest.

My arms will get cold if they leave the heated
table... I'm curled up inside, like Zeta.

Mitsugoshi's heated tables are amazing... You can't
get out once you're in... *flop*

*sigh*... It's a new year but everyone is completely
knocked out.

Alpha, being lazy during the New Year holiday is a
time-honored tradition where I grew up.

Those rules belong there. Here we have our own rules.
If you're all going to be pigs, then I will put away the
heated table.
Noooo, it's too soon!
Alpha, you demon! Fiend! Elf!

Yes, I'm an elf. What's wrong with elves? Come on,
follow Delta's example.
Yay!
Woow!!
Hahahaha!!!

How can she be so worked up in this cold? Stupid dogs
sure are stupid...

If we follow her example...the brains of the Shadow
Garden will rot... It will be a loss to the world.
Indeed, dogs will play, and children will laugh.

Oh, I've never heard that idiom before. Is it Shadow
Wisdom?
Um, kinda...

(Through Mitsugoshi, my knowledge of my past life that
I've taught Gamma and the girls is spreading throughout
this world.)

(Thanks to that, I can have a satisfying laze around
on New Year's just like in modern Japan. Although
speaking of New Year culture...)
Don't they make kagami rice cakes around here?
Kagami rice cakes? What are those?

Kagami rice cakes. They're made from rice, they're
round, white, and hard...

That's too vague. I can't imagine it. I might be able
to guess if I had your insight...

I know about rice cakes. Some therianathropes make
them by cooking warm rice. But aren't rice cakes
supposed to be soft?

That's one kind of rice cake... In other words,
kagami rice cakes change shape according to
the circumstances?

It's food, but it changes shape...? Isn't that slime?
Sounds interesting, but not delicious.

Alpha has certainly got the right idea, but...yeah,
it's hard to explain. I think you'd understand if
you see it.

Hey Eta, can't you research it and make some rice
cakes to put out for decoration?

Processed like a paste... That's common... Not
interesting.

It isn't a paste but a special rice cake with a
malleable shape, right, Cid?
Umm... I guess it's difficult to reproduce.

But we went to the trouble to have New Year's, so I
wanted to do something New Year-related.

If you want to eat it, then I will manage somehow to
find this kagami rice cake.

Really? It's probably unimportant around here, so
don't go overboard searching for it, okay?

If I can't even find kagami rice cakes, then I can't
be the leader of the Seven Shadows.

Look, Cid, this is a good chance to really prove our
strength.

(Did I hit an unnecessary switch? Well, anyway...this
could get interesting.)

No one here seems to know anything about it. Let me
ask the others.

No, Master Shadow hasn't blessed me with such special
wisdom.
We don't sell any food at Mitsugoshi with such a name.

I have access to various cakes in my position, but I've
never heard of those kind of cakes.
No good. I've tried everyone.

But I made such a big deal about it, so I can't
exactly go ask Cid now...

Ha-ruff. What's up Lady Alpha? You lookin' for kagami
rice cakes?

I don't think you know about them, Delta. Now where
can I find kagami rice cakes...
Yeah, I know about 'em.

Exactly, it was a waste of time asking youwait,
what?!!

This may be the first time I've seen Lady Alpha so
surprised...
Delta, do you really know about kagami rice cakes?

Yes. It's a rice cake recipe that has been passed
down in therianathrope villages. It's like a big
round mirror.

(A round...mirror. So it's hard. It seems to match
the description that Cid gave... Does Delta really
know of it?)

(That said, Zeta knew about rice cakes. So it isn't
strange that Delta, a fellow therianathrope, knows
it too. I should've considered that.)
Delta, I would like to have that kagami rice cake.
Should I show you? Can I go outside?

(She just wants to go for a walk... No, only Delta
has any clues about this. I will try believing her.)
Yes, can I ask for your help?

Okay! Right, let's get going to the Therianthrope
Shrine!

...Wait! The Therianthrope Shrine? Kagami rice cake
is there?
Yes!

The Therianthrope Shrine is some distance from here.
Once we head there we can't exactly just come back,
and if it's a shrine, then we should dress formally.
Lady Alpha, we should get going already!

If we have to go that far away, we need to prepare
for it.
But I don't care about that! Let's go, let's go!
Delta, did you not hear me?
...Eep! O-Okay...

2.Text:
Kagami rice cakes can be found at Great Ize Shrine,
the Therianthrope Shrine!
Great Ize Shrine... I've never heard of it.

Why is it that Zeta, another therianathrope, doesn't
know about it, but you do, Delta?

Zeta probably isn't interested. Recently, it's a
popular play area!
Play area? I thought a shrine would be a sacred spot.
Really? I don't get complicated stuff like that.

But I heard you can get a wonderful gift if you save
up your visitor points when you go to the shrine.

(It sounds like a theme park, but it IS a sacred
place, isn't it?)

They're supposed to give out kagami rice cakes at
the New Year's event!

I really don't understand what therianathropes are
thinking sometimes. I can't imagine anything
anymore...
Here we are!
This is...a sacred shrine, correct?
Yep!

There are balloons with characters on them...and
colorful but meaningless lights...

What exactly is sacred about this shrine? Is this not
entirely a theme park?

Don't look at me like that. I told you it was a play
place.

This questionable place looks as strange as I
expected. What a nightmare...

I don't know the complicated stuff, but this shrine's
actually got a thing called "history." Literal decades
of the stuff.
Back then, New Year events were supposed to be quiet

Welcome! Try some Mitsugoshi sweet sake, made from
fermented rice!

Mitsugoshi? You there, do you have a moment? Does
this shrine have some connection with Mitsugoshi?

Yes! We wanted to revitalize our village and have fun
like therianthropes are supposed to...
Mitsugoshi supported our idea.
I see... So that's how it is.

(Through Mitsugoshi, the carefree and cheerful nature
of therianthropes has been combined with Shadow's
Shadow Wisdom.)

(A strange reaction between the two has led to the
birth of this unusual shrine...)

Come, come! Warm your innards with some super
spicy red kitsune udon noodles!

Try our green tanuki soba noodles heaped with veggies
to drive off any nasty bugs for a healthy new year!

*sniff, sniff*... Smells super good! And it looks so
tasty, I'm drooling!

They're selling it at those stalls over there.
I'm just gonna go over
No you aren't.
Awoo... This kimono is tight and constricting...

It's good that I can easily use your kimono sash as
a leash.

Lady Alpha! Lady Alpha! They're selling sweet sake
over there! Can I drink some? Can I?

Just a moment. Excuse me, does this have alcohol
in it?
Of course not! Anyone can enjoy this deliciousness!

Oh, is that so... In that case, Delta, you may
have some.
Yay! *sniff, sniff*
Ahhhh! Warm, amazing, and not too sweet!
How about for you, milady?

Thank you for asking, but I'll pass. I'm afraid I
must refrain.

No worries, participants for the Great Ize-athlon
often refrain from drinking any so they can be
prepared for the main events.

The Great Ize-athlon...? Another term I've never
heard of...

It's three fun contests based on ascetic exercises,
passed down in the Great Ize Shrine.

The Great Ize-athlon rolls them into one, for everyone
to compete in.
Fun, I suppose...

Whoever clears the Great Ize-athlon with the best
results gets kagami rice cake.

Kagami rice cake! I didn't expect that information to
just fall into our laps.
Sounds fun! I wanna try the Great Ize-athlon!

Again, you immediately want to get involved... But I
suppose we should...

(We can get our hands on the kagami rice cake which
Cid had halfway given up on.)

(Between me and Delta, one of us will come out on top
and win the main prize.)

Alright, let's enter. It will be worth it just for
the prize.
Awoo! Great Ize-athlon!
You can sign up at the reception desk over there!

They will close to new entrants soon, so you'd better
hurry! Good luck!

My, oh my, I didn't think we'd be able to get kagami
rice cake so easily.

Let's try these contests and see what ascetic
exercises are like for therianathropes.

3.Text:
This year too, the beginning of the New Year is upon
us! It's the 3rd Great Ize-eathlon!
"This year too" kind of indicates a short history...

Now for the three ascetic exercises passed down at
Great Ize Shrine! They have been greatly changed
for an open competition!

For those with the amazing luck to get the most
points, you will receive specially made kagami
rice cakes!

The kagami rice cakes Boss man wants! Right, we gotta
win this!

Well, when it comes to physical strength you're in
a league of your own, Delta.
I will enter too, but I will take it easy...

Now, without further ado, the first contestThe
"Great Ize Fortune Dash"!

Contestants start from the big gate at the front of
the shrine! The goal is the mega rice cake at the
back of the shrine!

It's just a simple footrace. If that's the case, then
Delta is enough.

In that mega rice cake, you'll find many
fortune slips!
Huh?

Whoever can find the fortune slip for "Great
Fortune" first will be the winner!

We need speed and luck... So I do actually need to
get involved...

All participants, please go around to the big gate in
front of the shrine!
...Huh? Oh dear! Delta, let's go!
Huh? What's the hurry...?
Wow, so many people! I can't even see the start gate!

Beaten before we even began... The contest had
started before the rules were explained.

The win goes to whoever gets to the start point
first... We should have gone to the gate as soon as
we entered, without waiting for the explanation.

So this means we're gonna start from a long way
behind.
Meanwhile, the leading group can run pretty freely.

I was too careless. I thought it would be easy to get
kagami rice cake and take it home to Cid!

We can still win! This is just a handicap that makes
it fair for the rest of 'em!
Delta...
I'm gonna take them all out and get to first place!

...You're right, complaining about it here achieves
nothing.

Then let's get this started! In your positions!
Ready...
START!
Yaaaaaa!!!

Urk... The frontrunners are blocking the way!
We can't even start running.
To the front!!!
Delta!

(Even in the middle of this crowd, she is running at
tremendous speed, weaving in and out...!)

(Only a therianathrope can run like that... No, only
Delta can run like that!)
You're in my way! Move, move!
Wha! Stop pushing!
Ack, aaah! I'm gonna fall in!!!
Fall in...? Look at that, a hole opened up!

Gahhh!!! Hope those are just New Years bamboo
decorations!!!

(There are sharp bamboo sticks at the bottom of the
hole... Ouch, that's gotta hurt.)
You gotta jump over the pitfalls!

Arrgghh! There are arrows hitting the landing point!
We can't avoid them!!!

(Cool! So many red and white arrows flying around
when you jump!)
Aroo!

(You gotta land and roll forward! Then roll onto all
fours and keep your footing!)

What the! That dog! She is avoiding all of the rapid
fire ceremonial arrows!
Move, move! Today is Delta's day!
Huh? The runners at the back have already caught up?!
How are they keeping up...?
Where's the giant rice cake at?! There!
Grr... We haven't lost yet!
We gotta find the "Great Fortune" slip first!
*munch, munch, munch*
She's not even digging. She's eating the rice cake!!!
That's nuts! She'll eat the fortune slips!
Ptooey! I bit into something!
Nooo, she spat out a fortune slip!
Erm, what's this, errrr... "G-R-E-A-T"...
Damn! She got the "Great Fortune" slip!
"Great radish!"
I can still find it!
Another fortune slip! "Poof!"
"Try again!"
"Cat!"

*sigh* There's the lead group. I wonder how Delta is
doing.
"Great King!" "Lucky Later!" "Very Lucky Later!"
Don't tell me... They still haven't dug it out?!
No! Ahh! "Hit! One more try!"

What does "hit" even mean...? Come on, you need to
search properly. If you hold it up to the light, you
can see through it.

Oh, it's see-through! But there are so many letters,
so it's not "Great Fortune!"
I got something!
You guys...
"Great Cat!" "Great Fortune!" "Great Trouble!"
Huh? Did you just say...
I got it! "Great Fortune!" I'm the winn
GIVE IT TO ME!!!
Guargh!
I got the "Great Fortune" fortune slip!

You just hit him really hard and took it. That has to
be against the rules...

And there you have it! In the end, all therianthropes
solve problems through force! The win goes to the
canine therianthrope Delta!
Yay! I won! I'm the winner!
Seriously? What is it with therianathropes...?

4.Text:
The Great Ize-athlon! Which this year once again
brings together those proud of their skills or
strength in order to win kagami rice cake!

The winner of the first contest, the "Great Ize
Fortune Dash," is the canine therianthrope Delta!
Yaaaaa!!!
Hehehe, yay, yay!

Delta, you're showing off. What do you intend to do
if your name gets out and it starts affecting your
missions?
Awoo! I'm really sorry...

I understand that you can play around at this shrine,
but we're here to get kagami rice cakes for Cid.

There are still two ascetic exercises to go! Everyone,
do your best to turn your luck around!
Now for our next contest!
Whoa! What's that? It's a white round thingy!
It looks like a pillar of rice cake, but...
It is our annual custom! The "Laughing Rice Cake!"

He is saying it like it's common knowledge again.
This event is only in its third year...

The rules are simple! You have to cut the rice cake
pillar into the shape of the Rice Cake Deity...while
blindfolded!

Rice Cake Deity? What's that? Do you know it,
Lady Alpha?

I want to say that I obviously don't, but...maybe
it's that thing over there. The statue next to the
priest.
It's plump. And so cute!

No, even if it's some kind of deity, don't call it
cute.

By the way, Rice Cake Deity goods are on sale at the
stall over there!
This shrine is really going to get cursed!

The time limit is 10 minutes. Let's see who can get
closest to the image of the Rice Cake Deity!

Later, we can all enjoy the deliciousness of the
statues you create!
Urk...this'll be hard. Seems kinda complicated.

You're great at breaking things but not so good at
making them.
But...I'll do my best! Blindfold me, please!
Go go go go go goooooo!
Umm... Maybe it'd be better if she stopped now?
Indeed.

Whew! Did I make the Rice Cake Deity? I'm sure a
miracle came outta these claws!
It's a shame, but miracles don't sell that cheap.
This is... Was it always a messed up rice cake?
The results are in! Delta's Rice Cake Deity gets...
Zero points!
Awoooooo!

Now the comments from the judging committee. "She has
desecrated art," "I saw something like this in a dream when
I was sick," and "Don't waste food."
Noooo...

That last comment sounds like a complete rejection of
the contest...

Currently, the participant Unkei has the highest
score at 98! Will there be a challenger who can
beat that score?!

I didn't even come close. I'll just cheer you on,
Lady Alpha.

So it's come to this. I will avenge you, Delta. I had
figured that this one was too much for you.

Surely, you know that your claws can't carve out the
plump form of the Rice Cake Deity.

Gah... But isn't it the same for you,  Lady Alpha?
Swords are only good for cutting straight...
Well, just watch. You there, please blindfold me.
Yes, just a moment.

Okay, the blindfold's on. How is it? Can you see how
many fingers I'm holding up?
Of course not. I'm blindfolded.
Haha, then it's okay!

Now to begin... But first, may I touch the real Rice
Cake Deity statue?
Yes, you may...

(I am not able to see it, but I can sense it... For
example, I could sense that therianthrope held
up three fingers just now.)

(Even without touching it, I can sense its shape to a
certain degree. You have no place in the Shadow
Garden if you can't even do that much.)

(I musn't use my eyes, but instead see with my heart.
Feel the shape of its soul... And strike.)

(So this is what you meant, Shadow. "Feel, do not
think" ...Now I understand).

Okay, I've finished. I want to start before I forget
anything.
R-Right, okay...start!
Yes!

(With the ferocity of fire and fluid elegance of water,
I pledge my blade to the Rice Cake Deity in my
mind's eye!)

Wow, amazing! I can see what you are doing, but I
can't do it like that!

(It's almost finished. As my heart desires, and as the
Rice Cake Deity's soul demands... My blade sings!)
Hah! Haaaaa!
I am finished.
Woooaaa!
Awoo! It looks exactly like the real thing!

The judging committee has voted! What score will
Alpha receive!?

100 points! There is no score higher! That makes it
the top score! The judges have no criticisms!
Wow, you did it! That's Lady Alpha for you!
Naturally.

But why'd you use a different sword move than usual?
You were so slow to carve it.

With so many eyes on us in public, if I were to use
Shadow Garden swordplay that might expose our
identities, wouldn't it?

This sword... Compared to my slime sword it is shaped
quite differently, so I adapted my swordplay to it, if that
makes sense.
Adapt...? I don't get it but okay!

All of the scores have been tallied! Alpha is ahead
with 100 points!

Well, I got a win and a loss! But I'll win in the
end!

(So far, so good...but is the kagami rice cake prize
really what Cid is after?)

(He will be disappointed if it is something completely
different.)

Alpha's statue is so impressive, we're going to put
it next to the kagami rice cake prize!

So that's kagami rice cake...it really is a mirror-
shaped rice cake. It's so big I would struggle to
hold it with my hands...

(It seems thinner than what Cid described, but it does
match his description of a mirror shape. I wonder if
he realizes how much trouble we are going through
to get it...)

Delta, whatever the last contest is, let's give it
our all.
Of course!

5.Text:
The Fortune Dash and the Laughing Rice Cake
events are over!

Finally we are getting to the last contest! "Hagoita
Deathmatch"! Only one participant will be crowned
overall winner and get their hands on the kagami
rice cake!

I wonder how they decide who the winner is. Also,
who came in second or third place in the first
contest?
They decide in order of who was closest!

Hmm... Therianthropes can be so vague. Although, some
participants look quite high-strung...

There'll be no problems if one of us wins the final
Hagoita Deathmatch!
Optimistic of you... Though you are right about that.

But more exactly, what is a Hagoita Deathmatch?
It sounds like a very dangerous event.

The rules are simple! It is a 1-on-1 titanic battle
using a racket and a calligraphy brush!

If you hit the shuttlecock with your racket but it
lands on your side, then you lose! But hitting
the shuttlecock with your calligraphy brush is
against the rules!

He said it was simple, but it's more complex than the
other contests. Are these really the correct rules...?

According to Cid, if you lose then you're supposed to
have your face painted in black ink...

Furthermore, you can interfere with your opponent by
using your calligraphy brush to throw ink. Direct attacks
using your brush or racket are forbidden! Only savages
use brute force to win!

You just hit him really hard and took it. That has to
be against the rules...

And there you have it! In the end, all therianthropes
solve problems through force! The win goes to the
canine therianthrope Delta!
Isn't that the opposite of what he said before?
It's fine as long as it's interesting.

There are other detailed rules too, like you can't
keep the shuttlecock with your racket.

If you do that, it's a foul, and you'll lose a point.
As for the other rules, you'll figure it out! Let's
get started!

Wait, it's a point system? How many points do you
start with?

Round 1, match 1! In the red corner! The Great Ize
Fortune Dash winner, Delta!
Awooo! I'm fired up!
Corner? Ah, I can't keep up with all this.

In the white corner! The winner of last year's Hagoita
Deathmatch! McKen Ro!

This year is my season! I'm gonna roll to the samba
beat!

It's coming! The McKen Samba Style! How will Delta
take on such a formidable foe?!

I can't move well with a brush. I wanna have another
racket instead.

What? The Niita-ryu dual racket style? That
legendary school that disappeared hundreds
of years ago...

Who would have though we'd see a revival of Niita-ryu
in this day and age...
...This event really is in its third year, right?
I'm gonna hit that shuttlecock!
Gyaaah!

Awoo! A strong smash hits McKen directly in the face!
He can't stand up. He loses by violent knockout!
I'm still fired up!

Huh... I should watch carefully and learn as much
of the rules as I can until my turn comes.

Now, the last match of round 1! In the white corner,
the winner of the Laughing Rice Cake! Alphaaaa!

I don't know why, but that title doesn't
ring well...

(But having watched all the matches up to now,
I'm starting to get the rules.)
Haaaaa!

Alpha chooses a straight hit! The shuttlecock flies
high in the sky!
Now!
Urgh, my eyes!

In that moment, she let fly with ink from her brush!
Admirable interference! Alpha gets the first point!

(Just two choices: get points the honest way by
hitting low and quick, or return high and slow
and throw ink for interference.)
Take this!

Oh, Alpha has hit it high again! But her opponent is
on to her!
You won't fool me twice!
You can't use the same hand!
Huh? Uwaaaghh!

Ahhh! She was aiming ink at his feet rather than his
face! He is sliding over the ink! He is down!

(Out of the two options, there's actually another
option. Read your opponent and distract them.
This contest is surprisingly complex.)

Who knew you could compete like this in Hagoita
Deathmatch! Alpha is starting a revolution!

...Or maybe I'm just the first to seriously devise
some tactics...

Now, this contest of Hagoita Deathmatch is heating up
into the finals! Deltaaaaa versus Alphaaaaaaa!

This will decide the winner of the Great Ize-athlon!
On whom will the kagami rice cake smile on?!

(At this point, we know that one of us is getting the
kagami rice cake. I don't care if I lose, but...)

Hehehe, just a bit more to victory! I've finished
off everyone by K.O. so far.

But Lady Alpha took forever to win her matches...
I'm stronger than her!
...What was that?
Eeek...!

It sounds like you have a misunderstanding. You need
some disciplining about who the victorious one is. Haaa!

Ahhh! Alpha hit the shuttlecock up high like before,
but she also threw her brush! Isn't a direct attack a
foul?!
(So fast! I can't avoid it!)

Delta guards her face with both rackets! The
calligraphy brush stopped between themright
at the tip of her nose!
Defending just as I expected.
Ack

Alpha jumps up high! She has caught up with the
floating shuttlecock!
Take some time to reflect!
Aroo!

The win is Alpha's! With a forbidden double smash shot
into Delta's face!
I...lost...

The rackets are destroyed, and Delta has lost the will
to fight. Alpha is victorious!

6.Text:
The overall champion of this year's Great Ize-athlon
is Alpha!

It was full of crazy contests. I guess those are
therianthropes for you...

Now we can get kagami rice cake! And give it to
Boss man!

We will now present the winner with kagami rice cake!
But before that...!

It did feel like they were holding something back
before the announcement... What now?
We will have an exhibition match of "Death Ending"!
Yeah! We've been waiting!

What on earth is a Death Ending... That sounds rather
alarming.
It's fine. There is nothing to be scared of.

This year's top two contestants! Delta, Alpha, this
way please!

You two will enter the cage with the beast, Shishi,
and give him the right to eat death!
Shishi? Delta, do you know about this?
Yeah. He's a big beast, but people-friendly.
(If Delta says so, then it should be okay.)

Playing with Shishi and letting him lick you will let
him eat the bad air and aura of death that surrounds
people.

It is the end of deathDeath Ending is an honor we
give to the top two contestants.

Very well...if it's part of the ceremony then we had
better finish it, or we will never get the kagami rice
cake.

Please, this way! Please go inside! We only just
caught him, but he is a messenger of the gods!

He's so big. I'll bet he breaks his opponent even if
he's just playing.
Thank you for clarifying that this is how he "plays."

Well, we could ask him to bite whatever part he likes,
legs or arms or head, and get this done with.
Huh? But take a good look at him...
What? Is there something else?
Grrr...
I knew it...! This isn't Shishi, it's Shishiodoshi.
It's a different animal? What will Shishiodoshi do?

He was just pretending to be Shishi to get close!
He'll swallow ya whole if you aren't ready!

They didn't see through Shishiodoshi's acting and
caught him thinking he is Shishi... Oh dear.
Grrr...

What is Shishiodoshi? He's not calm and tender and
likely to give up on us...?
More like he's hungry and wants a snack.
I thought so... We can't escape.

What should we do? Hunt him? Or stalk him and then
hunt him?

We can't do that. There are so many tourists at this
New Year festival.

If we make a big uproar, everyone will get thrown
into chaos, and we might cause an even bigger
disaster.

Also, if this event gets suspended, we won't be able
to get that kagami rice cake we've earned.

Ha-ruff... That'd mean we lose everything we worked so
hard for!
So to prevent that, let's deal with this quietly.
Grrrr... Slurrrrp.

We have to make it seem like he is licking our faces
and being playful, and then carefully hit him without
bringing attention to ourselves.

If we can stun him and make it look like he fell
asleep, to others it will look like he got tired and
dozed off.
...I see! Lady Alpha, you're sure amazing!
Grrr... Grraaaaahh!
This year's Shishi is really active!

But this year's winners are super strong too.
I'm getting all excited!

For better or worse, no one has noticed it is
Shishiodoshi. If possible, we need to end this
without them noticing...
All right, Delta. Slowly and quietly, okay?

Got it! Same as Boss man. Delta will be strong like
Boss man!
I'm not sure if you really understand...
Brrr... Grraaaaahh!

We need to take care of him before he eats us!
Discretely, like we're going to pet him...
Gaaahh!
He's got a hold of my head!
*chomp, chomp*
Ah, he's chewing on her! He's play-biting!
Play biting? These fangs hurt...!

Delta, even if it hurts, be patient. Now to make it
look like I'm going to pet him...
Graar, grarrr...!
Hahaha, he's opening his mouth!

The damage reached his internal organs. His mouth is
open wide because he's struggling to breathe.
Graaa!!
Ow! If he'd bitten down, it would've cut my throat.

Okay, now... We pretend to dance to get closer to
Shishiodoshi, and make it look like we are petting
him, then drive a blow into his belly!
Yeah! We'll teach you who is stronger!

7.Text: There there, shhhh!
Gr...guh... *crash*...
Ahh, Shishi is taking a rest!

Phew, we were able to disguise that he went
unconscious...

Never before has Shishi fallen asleep at Death
Ending... This is...
Lady Alpha, you okay?

Yes. If they had cancelled the presentation of the
kagami rice cake, all our efforts would have been
for nothing...

You two had some bad luck! But no worries, Shishi ate
all of the bad stuff!
Th-Thanks...

(He is always so easygoing... I wonder when and how
I can tell him that his Shishi is a fake...)

Give them a hand for their magnificent battle! Best
of luck to you in the future! Moving on, we present
winning contestant Alpha with the kagami rice cake!

(*sigh*... It really was a lot of trouble, but it is
finally over, and we now have the kagami rice
cake.)
Here you go! It's heavy, so take care holding it.
Thank you.

(It truly is beautiful. I can almost see my own
reflection in its flat surface).
Lady Alpha, you look so happy!

Oh, you can see it on my face? Well, we worked hard
for this.
Yeah, let's make Boss man happy!
Yes, let's surprise Cid. Let's go home!
You found kagami rice cake? Really?
Really! Show him, Lady Alpha!

Here, kagami rice cake that was given to us at the
Great Ize Shrine.
Huh? This is...?

(Wisdom has been recreated pretty faithfully up to
now, but in this case kagami rice cakes turned out
to be something unique to this world, even if they
didn't change the name.)
How...interesting.
What? Is there something wrong?
No, nothing. Well done, Alpha.

Hehe, just doing my job. So you said you have to put
the kagami rice cake somewhere? Where?

It's bigger and bulkier than I thought. Actually, I
want to put it over there, but...

You went through all of that to get it, so why don't
we eat it with everyone? I wonder what it tastes like.

Graaarf! I'm starving 'cause we did so much exercise.
Lady Alpha told me not to buy or eat anything!

My apologies. We entered the Great Ize-athlon, and
then I wanted to get the prize to you quickly...

Looks like you two worked hard, so I'll do the
cooking.

Oh, you'll do it yourself? You don't have to if you
don't want to, okay? Though...I would enjoy your
cooking.

At the very least, I can just grill or boil it.
Ah, seasoning is also important.

Soy sauce, roasted soybean flour, adzuki beans for
red bean soup... I've got this.

Well, certainly I could ask Zeta and the others to
research it...
I want to eat Boss man's homemade food!
Right, it's settled! So what sounds best?

If I grill it with soy sauce, it'll be salty. Roasted
soybean flour will make it sweet, I think. I'd
have to powder it with flour.

If you make it powdery, Delta will blow off all the
flour.
I don't like stuff that's too salty or sweet. Yuck.

Then I think red bean soup is the winner. The beans
are naturally sweet, but I think you'll like it.

Red bean soup! Red bean soup! What kinda food it is?
I don't care, I wanna eat it!

It'll be fun to try making it. This kagami rice cake
is massive, so there should be plenty for all of
the Seven Shadows.
In the meantime I'll gather everyone together, then.
Here you go. This is red bean soup.
A soup dish... Soup?

There are bits of rice cake, and it smells sweet...
Maybe it's a comfort food? Good for cold days or
when you feel tired?

I see... So kagami rice cakes are pliable. So many
forms... Stretched or even filled with air. It's just as
you said, Cid.

It's still hot, so be careful not to burn your
tongue.
Grrrr, grrrrrr...
Haha. Hey dog, isn't it hot for your tongue?
Not at all! *gulp* Grrrrr!
This rice cake... It's so stretchy.

Grrr... You're on, Zeta! Let's see who can stretch it
the most!

*sigh*... If you're trying to sell a fight, I've got
no choice but to buy in. Can't let you think I'll
run away.

(Rice cake...soft when warm, hard when cool. This
might be the next big thing after slime...)

Hey, look at Epsilon. She's carefully checking how
stretchy it is.
Huh? Ohhhh, yes? I mean, yes!

Everyone, we had to say something before we started
eating.
Oh, sorry...

Hahaha, Delta is pretty hungry. Okay, everyone, let's
eat.
Let's eat!
So this is red bean soup...
How is it? I hope you like it.
Yes, it has a refined sweetness, and it warms you up.

Honestly speaking, you really surprised me when you
brought back this kagami rice cake. I kinda didn't
expect it.

Don't underestimate the potential of the Shadow
Garden. This is the power of the organization that
you created.

In fact, it's more of an organization that you
created.
I really didn't want to create it. But you...
*munch, munch* Arg...!
The stupid dog got a rice cake stuck in her throat!

It says in books that it will come out if you thump
her on the back!
Oh dear! Delta, are you okay?

(Dear me, this year started with an uproar. But...
It's not so bad to have a bit of chaos.)

(I hope that we can get through this year without
losing anyone...)
